<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Head and pronotum greenish yellow, posterior margin of crown with median and lateral spot on either side of median line, one lateral spot on anterior region of pronotum more widely placed than that on crown, dark brown; posterior and lateral margins of pronotum whitish with brown markings especially on lateral margins. Scutum and scutellum brownish yellow marked with dark brown and scutum with apex and one spot on each lateral margin ivory. Forewing ivory white with dark brown mottling, much rich on apical and subapical cells; median spot pale brown, semicircular, its anterior margin and larger lateral elongate oval spot, dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
Head polished, as wide as pronotum. Crown about half as long medially as pronotum, rather 
<taxonomicName box="[1322,1433,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
. Pronotum as long as combined length of scutum and scutellum, transversely wrinkled and polished.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis box="[199,363,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,546,571]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia
</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[377,435,546,571]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
pygofer posteriorly conically rounded with macrosetae confined to posterior 
<number box="[1301,1350,547,571]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="0.33">0.33</number>
region. Valve 
<taxonomicName box="[222,333,582,607]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
, twice as broad at base as long medially, posteriorly narrowed with rounded apex, lateral margins sinuate. Subgenital plate with well developed membranous apical process 
<number box="[991,1040,618,643]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="0.46">0.46</number>
times as long as total length. Style with well developed lateral subapical lobe, apophysis straight, transversely rugose. Connective with stem shorter than arms. Aedeagus with shafts elongate, simple, diverging in ventral view and curved dorsally in lateral view, with small 
<taxonomicName box="[277,386,726,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
lobe at midlength along inner margin, gonopore apical on ventral margin; ventral process in lateral view with straight ventral margin, 
<number box="[636,671,763,787]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="1.9">1.9</number>
times as long as shaft, triangularly expanded in distal third, then narrowed and thinly produced apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis box="[199,390,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite approximately twice as broad anteriorly as long medially; posterior margin rather concave laterally, medially produced into lobe with median short V-shaped excavation.
</paragraph>
