<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,258,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1086,1111]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species externally resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[716,851,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis box="[716,851,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Litura unda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the shape of the atrial process which is comparatively shorter and is strongly triangularly expanded before the apex in lateral view compared to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[376,462,1158,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis box="[376,462,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">L. unda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
